Cell.Data: Sorry, the name %1 is already taken. Please chose another name.
Are you sure you want to delete %1? All your items and progression will be lost.
You cannot have more than %1 active characters.
Are you sure you want to reset your attribute points?
Are you sure you want to reset your passive skill points?
No passive skill points have been assigned.
No attribute points have been assigned.
This action can only be performed in town.
Your Agility Gauge. This represents your investment into that Attribute compared to the expected value at your level.
Bonus Damage gained from the Attribute Points assigned to Agility.
Agility improves your Attack and Spell Casting Speed. Each point increases your Attack and Spell Casting Speed by %1.
The Bleed Ailment deals Rend Damage over Time to affected targets. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
The Burn Ailment deals Fire Damage over Time to the affected target and to enemies nearby, affecting up to 5 targets. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
The Curse Ailment increases the Damage received by the affected target. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
The Freeze Ailment prevents the affected target from moving or acting for a short time.
The Poison Ailment deals Toxic Damage over Time to affected targets. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
Your chance to apply Ailments with equipped weapon(s).
The Status Ailments capacity represents your ability to apply various Ailments on Enemies. Ailments can deal extra damage or afflict them with a debuff or crowd control.
The Shock Ailment deals Lightning Damage over Time to the affected target, and additional Lightning Damage to Shocked targets nearby. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
The Stasis Ailment slows the affected target's Movement, Attack, and Spell Casting Speed. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
The Stun Ailment prevents the affected target from moving or acting for a short time. The Ailment is not stackable.
The Weakness Ailment decreases the Damage dealt by the affected target. The Ailment can stack up to your Maximum Ailment Stacks value.
Bonus Damage gained from the Attribute Points assigned.
The global modifier to your Critical Chance with all weapons and skills.
The global modifier to your Critical Damage with all weapons and skills.
The global modifier of your Resistance against common Damage Types.
Your chance to deal a Critical Hit with Weapons and Attack Skills, determined by your Attack Critical Chance Score.
Your Attack Speed with Weapons and Attack Skills.
Your global Speed modifier with Melee Weapons Attacks.
A bonus added to your Base Attack Speed determined by your equipped Weapon, increasing your global Attack Speed.
The global Damage modifier from your 3 highest Attributes.
Rend Damage has a chance to apply the Bleed Ailment, dealing Damage over Time.
Your chance to apply the Bleed Ailment with Rend Damage of any source.

The Rend Damage dealt to a Bleeding Enemy each time the Bleed Ailment Ticks. The first Damage value displayed corresponds to one Bleed Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Bleed Stacks.
The duration of a Bleed Stack applied to an Enemy. This duration is reset when another Bleed stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Bleed.
Your chance to apply the Bleed Ailment, determined by your Bleed Chance Score.
The delay between each Tick of a Bleed Stack.
Determines how likely you are to Block incoming Damage. When Damage is Blocked, the Damage Taken is mitigated according to you Block Efficiency.
The percentage of Damage that will be mitigated from incoming Damage when you complete a Block.
Your chance to apply the Burn Ailment with Fire Damage of any source.
The Fire Damage dealt to a Burning Enemy each time the Burn Ailment Ticks. The first Damage value displayed corresponds to one Burn Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Burn Stacks.
The duration of a Burn Stack applied to an enemy. This duration is reset when another Burn Stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Burn.
Your chance to apply the Burn Ailment, determined by your Burn Chance Score.
The delay between each Tick of a Burn Stack.
How likely you are to inflict a Critical Hit with a Basic Attack. Critical Hits deal Critical Damage in addition to the Damage dealt by a Weapon.
Your Critical Damage multiplier with Weapons. Determines how much Critical Damage you deal when inflicting a Critical Hit on an Enemy.
Your chance to apply the Curse Ailment with Shadow Damage of any source.
The duration of a Curse Stack applied to an enemy. This duration is reset when another Curse Stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Curse.

The amount of additional Damage a Cursed Enemy will receive per Curse Stack. The first Damage value displayed corresponds to one Curse Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Curse Stacks.
The maximum amount of Status Ailments stacks that can be spread by the Curse Ailment each time it ticks.
The global spread Radius of the Curse Ailment you inflicts. Enemies within this range of the Curse source are eligible targets for the spreading of Status Ailments.
Your chance to apply the Curse Ailment, determined by your Curse Chance Score.
The delay between each tick of Status Ailment propagation from a Curse stack.
The base Damage dealt by your equipped Weapon(s).
The maximum Range of your Dash.
Transfer Time of Rage into Willpower and vice versa.

The Force Shield protects your Health from most Damage(except Ailment Damage) until it is empty. When the Force Shield Regeneration Delay is over, your Force Shield regenerates at the rate of your Force Shield Regeneration.
The amount of time required without taking Damage to activate your Force Shield Regeneration. Each time you receive Damage the Force Shield Regeneration Delay is reset.
The amount of Force Shield regenerated when the Force Shield Regeneration starts.
Your basic defensive capacities, representing your ability to reduce and avoid incoming Damage.
Modifier applied to your Dodge Chance.
Your global Passive Dodge Chance against all incoming attacks. The Passive Dodge completely ignores incoming Damage, regardless of its Type.
Your chance to apply an Ailment with an Attack, determined by your Attack Ailment Chance Score.
A modifier applied to your Status Ailment Resilience.
Your chance to apply an Ailment with a Spell, determined by your Spell Ailment Chance Score.
The average amount of Damage dealt per second with your equipped Weapon(s). This value is determined by your Weapon Damage and your Attack Speed.

Your Experience at your current Character Level. Reaching the Experience requirements for the next Level will raise your Character Level. You can gain Experience by killing Enemies and completing Quests.
The global duration modifier applied to Fear.
Your Ferocity Gauge. This represents your investment into that Attribute compared to the expected value at your level.
Bonus Damage gained from the Attribute points assigned to Ferocity.
Ferocity improves your Attack and Spell Critical Chance Score. Each Ferocity point increases your overall Critical Chance Score by %1.
Fire Damage has a chance to apply the Burn Ailment, dealing Damage over Time to you and nearby Allies.
Your chance to apply the Freeze Ailment with Frost Damage of any source.
The duration of the Freeze Ailment on an enemy.
The global duration modifier applied to Freeze.
Your chance to apply Freeze, determined by your Freeze Chance Score.
The global duration modifier applied to Frenzy.
Frost Damage has a chance to apply the Freeze Ailment, preventing affected targets from moving.
This Radius represents how close a Health Globe must be before you automatically pick it up.
Your global Gold Find modifier. Increases the amount of looted Gold.
This Radius represents how close Gold must be before you automatically pick it up.
Your Maximum Health. Your Health is depleted when you receive Damage. If your Health is depleted completely, you will enter a Downed state, or be killed if you have no Revive Tokens remaining.
Your Health Regeneration represents the amount of Health regenerated per Tick.
The time between each Healing Tick from your Health Regeneration and your Life Leech.
The amount of Damage you deal with Spells to fill your Life Leech Pool. The Life Leech Pool is consumed to restore your Health when your Health Regeneration Ticks.
The amount of Damage you deal with Attacks to fill your Life Leech Pool. The Life Leech Pool is consumed to restore your Health when your Health Regeneration Ticks.
Lightning Damage has a chance to apply the Shock Ailment, dealing Damage over Time.
Your Magic Find determines how likely you are to loot Uncommon Items.
The maximum number of each Ailment Stack that you can apply on a single enemy. Each Ailment stacks independently up to this maximum value.
Miscellaneous gameplay values which do not fall into one of the categories above.
Your basic Offensive capacities, representing your ability to perform Damage.
Physical Damage is the default Damage Type.
Toxic Damage has a chance to apply the Poison Ailment, dealing Damage over Time.
Your chance to apply the Poison Ailment with Toxic Damage of any source.

The Toxic Damage dealt to a Poisoned Enemy each time the Poison Ailment Ticks. The first Damage value displayed corresponds to one Poison Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Poison Stacks.
The duration of a Poison Stack applied to an enemy. This duration is reset when another Poison Stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Poison.
Your chance to apply the Poison Ailment, determined by your Poison Chance Score.
The delay between each Tick of a Poison Stack.

Your Presence determines how easy it is for Enemies to see and track you. A normal value for Presence is 100%. Below that, you become harder to target and see. At 0%, you are Invisible. At values higher than 100%, you are easier to spot and track.
The delay before Willpower Regeneration restarts after gaining Rage. Rage Conservation is not triggered by spending Willpower or Rage.
The amount of Rage Points generated each time you Hit an Enemy with a Weapon (except Staves).
The amount of Rage Points generated each time you are Hit by an Enemy.
The amount of Rage Points generated each time you kill an Enemy.
Your remaining Attribute Points. You earn Attribute Points each time you gain a Level, and you can use them to increase your Ferocity, Toughness, Agility and Wisdom.
Your basic Resistances to main Damage types. A positive Resistance will reduce part of the Damage you take from that Type, depending on the Damage value and the source Level.
Elemental Resistances determine your Damage Reduction from Fire, Frost and Lightning Damage Types.
Material Resistances determine your Damage Reduction from Physical, Toxic and Rend Damage Types.
Occult Resistances determine your Damage Reduction from Aether, Sacred and Shadow Damage Types.
Your passive Resistances to a specific Type of Damage. A negative Resistance means that you take more Damage of that Type.
Your Resource statistics, representing how you generate Resources of all kinds: Rage, Willpower and Stamina.
Your Resource Pool represents the maximum Resource Points you have at your disposal for both Willpower and Rage.
Sacred Damage has a chance to apply the Weakness Ailment, reducing the Damage you deal.
Shadow Damage has a chance to apply the Curse Ailment, increasing the Damage you take.
Your chance to apply the Shock Ailment with Lightning Damage of any source.

The Lightning Damage dealt to a Shocked Enemy each time the Shock Ailment Ticks. The first Damage value displayed corresponds to one Shock Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Shock Stacks.
The duration of a Shock Stack applied to an enemy. This duration is reset when another Shock stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Shock.
Your chance to apply the Shock Ailment, determined by your Shock Chance Score.
The delay between each Tick of a Shock Stack.
The global duration modifier applied to Snare and Root.
Your chance to deal a Critical Hit with Spells, determined by your Spell Critical Chance Score.
Your maximum number of Stamina Points available. Stamina allows you to use the Active Dodge.
The time it takes to regenerate a Stamina Point after using the Active Dodge.
Your chance to apply the Stasis Ailment with Aether Damage of any source.
The duration of a Stasis Stack applied to an rnemy. This duration is reset when another Stasis Stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Stasis.

How much Enemy's Movement, Attack, and Spell Casting Speeds are reduced by the Stasis Ailment. The first value corresponds to one Stasis Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Stasis Stacks.
Your chance to apply the Stasis Ailment, determined by your Stasis Chance Score.
The global duration modifier applied to Stun.
Your global Stun Resistance. Gives you a chance to completely ignore an incoming Stun.
Your chance to Stun, determined by your Stun Chance Score.
Your total Thorns Damage. Thorns are Physical Damage inflicted to enemies when they hit you and which pierce through their Protections.
The global Damage modifier applied to your Thorns Damage.
Your Toughness Gauge. This represents your investment into that Attribute compared to the expected value at your level.
Bonus Damage gained from the Attribute Points assigned to Toughness.
Toughness improves your Health and Force Shield. Each point increases your Health and Force Shield Bonus by %1.
Aether Damage has a chance to inflict the Stasis Ailment, slowing your Movement as well as your Attack and Spell Casting Speed.
The global modifier to the Willpower Cost of Spells. Lower costs reduce the amount of Rage generated.
The number of Willpower Points generated each time you Hit an Enemy with a Staff.
Your Willpower Regeneration per second. Also represents the Rage lost each second when the Rage Conservation delay is over.
Your chance to apply the Weakness Ailment with Sacred Damage of any source.
The duration of a Weakness Stack applied to an enemy. This duration is reset when another Weakness Stack is applied.
The global duration modifier applied to Weakness.
The amount of Enemy Damage Reduction by the Weakness Ailment. The first displayed value corresponds to one Weakness Stack, and the second represents the maximum number of Weakness Stacks.
Your chance to apply the Weakness Ailment, determined by your Weakness Chance Score.
The Damage you deal in one Hit with your equipped Weapon.
Your Wisdom Gauge. This represents your investment into that Attribute compared to the expected value at your Level.
Bonus Damage gained from the Attribute Points assigned to Wisdom.
Wisdom improves your Attack and Spell Ailment Chance Score. Each point increases your overall Ailment Chance Score by %1.
The amount of Health you receive when you take a red Health Globe.
The amount of Force Shield you receive when you take a red Health Globe.
The global Reduction applied to your Skills Cooldown.
Attribute points equally increase the Damage you deal.
The global Resource Reduction applied to all your Willpower Skills.
The global Resource Reduction applied to all your Rage Skills.
The amount of Rage you receive when you are Hit by an Enemy.
The additional bonus applied to your Health.
The additional bonus applied to your Force Shield.
